{"article_id":"1bL9XRigj349VPfG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"With the first Democratic debate in the books , a new CNN/ORC poll finds","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"most","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"who watched","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"think","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Hillary Clinton had the best performance of the night ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"but her strong showing has n't boosted her standing in the race for the party 's nomination .","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"Clinton stands at 45 % in the race for the Democratic nomination ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"with Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders behind her at 29 % .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Vice President Joe Biden ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"who is considering a run for presidency","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"and did not participate in last week 's debate ,","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"follows at 18 % .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Behind the top three , former Virginia Sen. Jim Webb had 1 % support ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"while former Rhode Island Gov . Lincoln Chafee , Harvard professor Larry Lessig and former Maryland Gov . Martin O'Malley all held less than 1 % support .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Compared with pre-debate polling ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"Sanders ' support is up five points since mid-September ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"but no other candidate showed significant change .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"As Biden mulls whether or not to get in the race ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"the poll suggests","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Democrats are becoming less enamored of a run from the vice president .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"In August , 53 % of registered Democrats said","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"they wanted Biden to run ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"that 's down to 47 % in the new poll .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Should Biden decide to sit out the race for the Democratic nomination ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"Clinton 's lead over Sanders climbs to 23 points :","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"56 % would back Clinton ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"33 % Sanders .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Overall , 31 % of registered Democrats say","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"they watched all or most of the CNN/Facebook debate ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"held October 13 in Las Vegas .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"More than 6-in-10 Democrats","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"who watched","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"say","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"Clinton did the best job ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"almost doubling the 35 %","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"who thought","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"Sanders had the best performance .","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"On the other side of the coin , 43 % of those","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"who watched","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"Chafee had the worst night ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"31 % thought","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"Webb did ,","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"12 % O'Malley .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"Among those Democrats","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"who watched the debate ,","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"both Sanders and Biden are viewed more favorably","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"than they are among Democratic voters generally :","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"Sanders ' favorability number bumps from 62 % among all Democratic voters to 84 % among debate viewers ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"while Biden climbs from 76 % to 89 % favorable .","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"Clinton 's numbers are about the same in both groups .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Despite their positive feelings toward Biden ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"debate-watchers are more apt than others to say","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"Biden should stay out of the contest","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"( 61 % think","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"he should not run ,","depth":15},{"id":57,"text":"compared with 43 % of those","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"who did not watch )","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"and they are far more likely to be satisfied with the Democratic field generally","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"( 84 %","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"compared with 64 % among those","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"who did n't watch ) .","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"Assessing the lesser-known candidates ,","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"debate-watchers are more positive than other Democrats toward O'Malley ,","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"( 44 % favorable","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"compared with 20 % among Democratic voters generally ) .","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"But Webb and Chafee are both viewed more negatively among those","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"who watched","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"( For Chafee , 32 % unfavorable among debate-watchers vs. 18 % among all Democratic voters ;","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"Webb is at 37 % unfavorable among debate-watchers , 20 % among all Democratic voters ) .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Following the debate ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Clinton continues to dominate as the more trusted candidate across several top issues , with double-digit advantages over Sanders and Biden as the candidate","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"who would best handle the economy , health care , foreign policy , race relations , climate change and gun policy .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"Clinton also now holds a small edge over Sanders as most trusted on income inequality","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"( 43 % Clinton , 38 % Sanders ) .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Debate-watchers are more likely than others to say","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"they trust Sanders on top issues ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"though even among this more-friendly audience , he continues to trail Clinton on most issues .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"Exceptions are income inequality","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"( 50 % of debate-watchers trust Sanders","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"vs. 36 % for Clinton )","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"and climate change","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"( 40 % each say","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"Clinton and Sanders would be best able to handle that ) .","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"Sanders gained no ground , however , on foreign policy .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"On that question , Clinton 's strength grows among those","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"who watched :","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"77 % in that group say","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"they trust her most","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"to handle foreign policy , up from 66 % among Democratic voters overall .","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"On two issues","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"where the debate highlighted differences among the candidates ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"fissures within the Democratic electorate","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"on who would best handle them","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"emerge .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"Income inequality appears to be the most divisive issue ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"with women , older voters , those without college degrees , moderates and those with lower incomes more apt to trust Clinton on the issue ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"while those with college degrees , liberals , and urbanites are more likely to favor Sanders .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"And on gun policy , there 's a sharp gender divide .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Women are far more likely to say","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"they trust Clinton","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"to handle it","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"than men , 50 % to 37 % .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Democratic gun owners are more evenly split on the question ,","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"with 35 % saying","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"they trust Clinton most on gun policy , 27 % Sanders and 21 % Biden .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Among those Democrats","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"who do not own guns ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"it 's 48 % Clinton , 21 % Biden and 16 % Sanders .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Overall , Democrats are n't much more satisfied with their field now","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"than they were in July","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"before any debates had happened .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"While the share `` very satisfied '' has risen from 26 % to 33 % ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"the share","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"they are at least fairly satisfied","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"has held steady at about 7-in-10 .","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"Women do report","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"feeling more satisfied with the field than men ,","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"but younger Democrats , a key group for Barack Obama 's general election victories , are far less satisfied with this field of candidates than older Democrats .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"Only about one-quarter of those under age 50 say","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"they are very satisfied ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"compared with 40 % of those age 50 or older .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"When matched against the top candidates from the Republican field ,","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"Clinton , Sanders and Biden all top Donald Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"who has been leading most polling on the Republican nomination contest since this summer .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"But Biden is the only one","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"who holds a significant lead over Ben Carson , a more recent addition to the top of the Republican field .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"Trump trails Clinton by 5 ,","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Sanders by 9","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"and Biden by 10 .","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"But against Carson , both Clinton","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"( 47 % to Carson 's 48 % )","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"and Sanders","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"( 46 % to Carson 's 48 % )","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"run about evenly with the former neurosurgeon .","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"Biden tops Carson by 8 points .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"The CNN/ORC International Poll was conducted by telephone October 14-17 among a random national sample of 1,028 adult Americans .","depth":3},{"id":139,"text":"Results among the 425 registered voters","depth":5},{"id":140,"text":"who say","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"they are Democrats or independents","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"who lean toward the Democratic Party","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"have a margin of sampling error of plus or minus 5 percentage points .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":287,"left":0,"right":286,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":286,"left":280,"right":285,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":149,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":6,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":1,"right":147,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":147,"left":146,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":159,"right":278,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":159,"left":156,"right":158,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":7,"right":155,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":8,"right":154,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":151,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":9,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":157,"right":17,"relation":